title: Liam Lynch - Discography
description:
6 Liam Lynch albums and a couple bonus tracks.

You may know Liam Lynch from his hit song "United States Of Whatever"He also was a co-creator of the Sifl & Olly show, as well as doing all kinds of work in film and music videos including Tenacious D, Sarah Silverman, and Foo Fighters.


Full albums:
Eel (1995)
We're All-Nighters (2001)
Fake Songs (2003) - includes 3 b-sides
How To Be A Satellite (2006)
Get Up On The Raft (2008)
The Middle (2011)

All rips are as high of a quality as I could get them. v0 mp3s are because they were downloaded from Amazon as that, all others are 320 mp3s converted from FLAC using dBpoweramp with LAME 3.99.


This is an updated version of my previous Liam Lynch torrent. You should be able to save this on over the old one without losing anything. I was lucky enough to purchase a copy of Eel (it's so rare! i'm so happy!) and rip it to include this time around, at high quality.


I'm a huge fan of Liam and he's an amazing songwriter and musician, and a very hard worker. If you dig his stuff... it's all available online (itunes, amazon), so don't be afraid to show your appreciation. :) :)
